Unum Group NYSE: UNM is a Chattanooga, Tennessee-based Fortune 500[2] insurance company formerly known as UnumProvident.[3] Unum Group was created by the 1999 merger of Unum Corporation and The Provident Companies[3] and comprises three distinct businesses –  Unum US, Unum UK, and Colonial Life. Its underwriting insurers include The Paul Revere Life Insurance Company and Provident Life and Accident Insurance Company.[1] Unum is the top disability insurer in both the United States and United Kingdom[4] and also offers other insurance products including accident, critical illness and life insurance.[5]
As of December 2013, Unum had 9,200 full-time employees and annual revenue of $10.35 billon.[1] Thomas Watjen has led Unum as its CEO since 2003.[6]



