IT Budget




Unum Group, formerly known as Union Mutual Life Insurance Company, was founded in 1848 and became the Unum Corporation in 1986. In 1998 Unum Corporation merged with Provident, which had recently acquired the Paul Revere Corporation, forming the UnumProvident Corporation. In 2007… MoreUnum Group, formerly known as Union Mutual Life Insurance Company, was founded in 1848 and became the Unum Corporation in 1986. In 1998 Unum Corporation merged with Provident, which had recently acquired the Paul Revere Corporation, forming the UnumProvident Corporation. In 2007 the name was shortened to Unum. Unum Group is based in Chattanooga, TN. The company offers group and individual income protection products in the United States and the United Kingdom. It also provides a portfolio of other insurance products, including long-term care insurance, life insurance, employer and employee-paid group benefits and related services.
Unum Group, formerly known as Union Mutual Life Insurance Company, was founded in 1848 and became the Unum Corporation in 1986. In 1998 Unum Corporation merged with Provident, which had recently acquired the Paul Revere Corporation, forming the UnumProvident Corporation. In 2007… MoreUnum Group, formerly known as Union Mutual Life Insurance Company, was founded in 1848 and became the Unum Corporation in 1986. In 1998 Unum Corporation merged with Provident, which had recently acquired the Paul Revere Corporation, forming the UnumProvident Corporation. In 2007 the name was shortened to Unum. Unum Group is based in Chattanooga, TN. The company offers group and individual income protection products in the United States and the United Kingdom. It also provides a portfolio of other insurance products, including long-term care insurance, life insurance, employer and employee-paid group benefits and related services.

IT Priorities

 • Over the next 6-12 months Unum Group will focus on implementing data warehousing appliances. 

IT Structure

 Unum Group's Information Technology department operates out of several locations. However, the majority of staff members are located in the company's Tennessee-based headquarters and in Maine. Internal IT also works closely with product development and general technology staff to streamline technologies throughout the company's infrastructure. 

IT Intelligence Snippets

2013:
•100 tb – 1 pb data volume company-wide across 2 to 5 data centers, and expects an annual data growth of 20-50%. 
•75-90% of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of 2013. 
•Corporate IT manages 1200 mobile devices. 
•Corporate IT manages 1000 desktops. 
•Standardized on 1-2 product vendors with a limited set of hardware. 
•Data center strategy is centered on whatever is best for applications – VMs/standalone server/custom hardware appliance.
•Long term plan for running new applications is to add servers and virtualize, but no new facilities are scheduled.

Unum Group's IT budget is typically finalized in Q4





